00:14:06.858 --> 00:14:12.228
lawyers and writers no doubt felt
some sorrow about this, but felt

00:14:12.388 --> 00:14:14.398
that their jobs were perfectly safe.

00:14:14.948 --> 00:14:18.618
After all, a robot could never
completely replace them, right?

00:14:19.638 --> 00:14:25.118
But it’s clear that, at least on the
lower end, the more mass-produced

00:14:25.118 --> 00:14:28.838
and unoriginal end, yes they can.

00:14:29.588 --> 00:14:33.738
We’ve seen this already with
generic blog content, but it

00:14:33.738 --> 00:14:35.568
has even spread to newspapers.

00:14:36.228 --> 00:14:41.778
Many news articles about things like
lower league sporting fixtures or company

00:14:41.778 --> 00:14:47.968
